HEADWORD: Bevelled
<hw>Bev"elled</hw> }</mhw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Formed to a bevel angle; sloping; <as>as,
the <ex>beveled</ex> edge of a table</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>Replaced by two planes inclining
equally upon the adjacent planes, as an edge; having its edges replaced
by sloping planes, as a cube or other solid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bevel gear</ent>⟦br⟧
